We want to inform you that whenever you use our Service, in a case of an error in the app we collect
data and information (through third-party products) on your phone called Log Data. This Log Data may
include information such as your device Internet Protocol (“IP”) address, device name, operating
system version, the configuration of the app when utilizing our Service, the time and date of your use
of the Service, and other statistics.
4. Log Data
Cookies are files with a small amount of data that are commonly used as anonymous unique identifiers.
These are sent to your browser from the websites that you visit and are stored on your device’s internal
memory.
5
.
Cookies and Other Tracking Technologies
This Service does not use these “cookies” explicitly. However, the app may use third-party code and
libraries that use “cookies” to collect information and improve their services. You have the option to
either accept or refuse these cookies and know when a cookie is being sent to your device. If you
choose to refuse our cookies, you may not be able to use some portions of this Service. PHZ doesn’t
guarantee Service to be fully functional without the aid of cookies.
In addition to cookies, PHZ may use other now and later developed tracking technologies. Users will
be notified of use of such tracking technologies.
6. Service Providers
We may employ third-party companies and individuals due to the following reasons:
To facilitate our Service;
To provide the Service on our behalf;
Personalization of content, recommendations and targeting of advertisement;
Handling of Customer Service for Purchases and the Service;
Fraud prevention and to enforce the Terms of the Services;
To ensure the users’ compliance with the Terms of the Services and this Privacy Policy;
For market research;
To maintain and develop cyber security;
To ensure the functioning and maintenance of the Services;
To perform App related services; or
To assist us in auditing and analyzing how our Service is used.
We want to inform users of this Service that these third parties have access to their Personal
Information. The reason is to perform the tasks assigned to them on our behalf. However, they are
obligated not to disclose or use the information for any other purpose.
7. Security
We value your trust in providing us your Personal Information, thus we are striving to use
commercially acceptable means of protecting it. But remember that no method of transmission over the
internet, or method of electronic storage is 100% secure and reliable.
8
. Links to Other Sites
This Service may contain links to other sites. If you click on a third-party link, you will be directed to
that site. Note that these external sites are not operated by us. Therefore, we strongly advise you to
review the Privacy Policy of these websites. We have no control over and assume no responsibility for
the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party sites or services.
9. Children’s Privacy
These Services do not address anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally
identifiable information from children under 13 years of age. In the case we discover that a child under
13 has provided us with personal information, we immediately delete this from our servers. If you are a
parent or guardian and you are aware that your child has provided us with personal information, please
contact us so that we will be able to do the necessary actions.
If you believe that we might have any information from or about a child under the age of 13, please
contact us at support@phz.fi.
10. Data Retention
We will retain your Personal Data only for as long as is necessary for the purposes set out in this
Privacy Policy or permitted by law. We will retain and use your Personal Data to the extent necessary
to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our legal agreements.
If the data is stored and used only to ensure User-PHZ -communication (e.g. the contact form is used to contact PHZ) and there are no legal obligations to store the personal data, the data will be stored either until all communication between PHZ and the User ceases or until the user requests for their personal data to be removed, but no longer than six years.
11. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Thus, you are advised to review this page
periodically for any changes. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on
this page.
12. Governing Law
This privacy policy is governed by the laws of Finland, and any dispute shall be carried out in Helsinki
District Court, Finland, in Finnish language.
13. Rights of the Registered Person
The users of our Services are entitled to review, correct, update and have removed any Personal Data
collected on him/her and stored in the register. When a user wishes to use the above right, he or she
should send a signed request thereof to PHZ using the contact details below.
